📊 Recruitment Metrics Dashboard – Power BI Project
This project is an interactive Recruitment Metrics Dashboard developed in Power BI, designed to help HR and recruitment teams monitor and analyze key hiring and workforce metrics.

🚀 Features
Total Employee Overview – Displays total workforce count.

Gender-Based Insights – Utilizes DAX to dynamically split and calculate:

Total Male Count: 485

Total Female Count: 515

Headcount by City & Department – Drilldown view of employee distribution by location and team.

Business Unit Insights – Gender-wise headcount across corporate, manufacturing, and research units.

Compensation Analysis – Tracks average annual salary and bonus by job role and department.

Interactive Filters – Slicers for department, city, and business unit to enable dynamic filtering.

🛠️ Technologies Used
Power BI Desktop

DAX (Data Analysis Expressions)

Data visualization techniques: bar charts, pie charts, KPIs, and interactive slicers

🎯 Objective
To provide data-driven insights into recruitment performance and workforce demographics, enabling better decision-making around hiring, diversity, and compensation planning.
